---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Chatbot from '../components/Chatbot.astro';
---
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
</head>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <Header />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <a class="inline-flex items-center text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 mb-8" href="/">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 19l-7-7 7-7M19 12H5"/>
      </svg>
      Back to registration
    </a>

    <div class="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: June 16, 2025</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-600">

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">PRIVACY POLICY OF THE WEBSITE "https://mytherapyspaces.com/"</h2>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1. IDENTIFICATION OF THE DATA CONTROLLER</h3>
          <ul class="list-none space-y-2">
            <li>Name: Unicage Soft Programming Laboratory Software Europe, Lda.</li>
            <li>Address: TEC LABS - Innovation Center, Campus da FCUL, Campo Grande, 1749-016 Lisboa</li>
            <li>Tax ID: 513740163</li>
            <li>Phone: +351 912478455</li>
            <li>E-mail: info@unicage.com</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. INFORMATION OBLIGATION</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">The protection of personal data of individuals is safeguarded in Portugal by Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 ("GDPR") and by Law No. 58/2019, of 8 August, which ensure the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and the free movement of such data.</p>
          <p class="mb-3">"Personal data" means any information, of any nature and regardless of its support, including sound and image, relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, so protection does not cover data of legal entities. A person is considered identifiable who can be identified directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identification number or to one or more specific elements of their physical, physiological, mental, economic, cultural or social identity (for example, their name associated with their phone number or their email address).</p>
          <p class="mb-3">For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, representatives of Study Centers, Teachers and Students will be referred to as "Users / User". References to "Professionals" do not include Students.</p>
          <p>By reading this Privacy Policy, the User is informed about the processing of their personal data carried out by Unicage Soft Programming Laboratory Software Europe, Lda. ("Unicage") through the website https://mytherapyspaces.com/ ("Website").</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. MINORS</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">Unicage does not intentionally allow users under 13 years of age to register on the Website without the prior consent of their respective parental responsibility holders.</p>
          <p class="mb-3">If Unicage becomes aware of the collection of personal data from a user under 13 years of age through the Website, without the consent of the respective parental responsibility holder, it will take the necessary actions to delete such data.</p>
          <p>If you are the holder of parental responsibilities for a user under 13 years of age registered in our service without your consent, please contact our service through the email address info@unicage.com to request the deletion of such personal data from our system.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. PURPOSES OF PERSONAL DATA PROCESSING</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">The personal data that Unicage collects and otherwise processes through the Website will be used solely for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-3">
            <li>Manage the use of the Website and ensure the provision of services available therein</li>
            <li>Provide support and communicate with Users, particularly following requests for information, complaints or technical support requests</li>
            <li>Dissemination of information and/or campaigns, promotions and news about services provided through the Website</li>
            <li>Analysis of service usage to identify User habits and trends in order to improve services offered and meet specific User needs</li>
            <li>Compliance with legal obligations to which Unicage is bound or defense of rights that assist it</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mb-3">Unicage guarantees the confidentiality of all data provided. Notwithstanding that Unicage proceeds with the collection and processing of data in a secure manner that prevents its loss or manipulation, using the most appropriate techniques for this purpose, it should be noted that data collection on open networks does not allow the circulation of personal data under conditions of absolute security, with the risk of these being accessed and used by unauthorized third parties.</p>
          <p>When applicable, failure to respond to data marked as mandatory may result in the impossibility of responding to the data subject's request.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. LEGITIMACY FOR PERSONAL DATA PROCESSING</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">Unicage processes User data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-3">
            <li>When they express their free, specific, informed and unambiguous consent for the processing of their personal data for certain purposes</li>
            <li>When necessary for the execution of a contract in which the User is a party, or for pre-contractual measures at the User's request</li>
            <li>For compliance with legal obligations to which Unicage is bound</li>
            <li>For the purposes of legitimate interests pursued by Unicage or third parties, except where such interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject requiring the protection of personal data</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mb-3">The User guarantees that the information provided is true, accurate, complete and updated, and is responsible for any damage or loss, direct or indirect, that may be caused as a result of the breach of this obligation.</p>
          <p>In case the data provided belongs to a third party, the User guarantees that they have informed said third party of the aspects contained in this document and obtained their authorization to provide their data to Unicage for the indicated purposes.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. RETENTION PERIOD</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">Unicage only retains personal data for the period that proves necessary or mandatory to fulfill the purposes described above, applying information retention criteria appropriate to each processing and in line with applicable legal and regulatory obligations.</p>
          <p class="mb-3">Unicage maintains personal data in its systems so that it is possible to identify data subjects according to the following criteria:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2">
            <li>During a period of time not exceeding the pursuit of the purposes for which they were collected, provided that legal or contractual obligations do not provide otherwise</li>
            <li>To comply with specific legal or contractual obligations</li>
            <li>When applicable and legitimate, until any request for opposition or deletion by the data subject</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. DATA COMMUNICATION</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">In addition to communications made in compliance with legal obligations, the personal data of the data subject may be known, in addition to Unicage, by partners and subcontractors, exclusively for the purposes of providing the contracted service, namely:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2">
            <li>Email services</li>
            <li>Information Technology Services, namely application management and administration, infrastructure provision and analytics</li>
            <li>Audit services and other similar services</li>
            <li>Payment and fraud control services</li>
            <li>Other service providers in the areas of support and consultancy for Unicage's activity</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS</h2>
          <p>In case of eventual processing of personal data outside the European Economic Area, this will only occur by adopting appropriate guarantees and the required level of protection, in accordance with legislation on the protection of personal data.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. INFORMATION SECURITY</h2>
          <p>Unicage has implemented appropriate technical and organizational security measures to ensure the security of personal data provided to it by the User, aiming to prevent its alteration, loss, processing and/or unauthorized access, taking into account the current state of technology, the nature of the data stored and the risks to which they are exposed.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. EXERCISE OF RIGHTS</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">In accordance with the provisions of the GDPR, the User may exercise their rights of access, rectification, deletion and, when applicable, limitation of processing, portability, opposition and withdrawal of consent, requesting it in writing by any of the following means, specifying the right or rights they wish to exercise:</p>
          <ul class="list-none space-y-2">
            <li>E-mail: info@unicage.com</li>
            <li>Postal address: Teclabs, Campus da FCUL, Campo Grande, 1749-016 Lisboa, Portugal</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">11. SUPERVISORY AUTHORITY</h2>
          <p>The User also has the right to lodge a complaint with the National Data Protection Commission regarding matters related to the exercise of their rights and the protection of their personal data, through the following web page https://www.cnpd.pt.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">12. THIRD PARTY PAGES</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">The Website may contain advertising, links or other content that link or redirect to pages and services of Unicage suppliers, advertisers, affiliates, sponsors and other third parties.</p>
          <p>However, Unicage does not control the content or links that appear on those pages and is not responsible for the practices used by those pages or Websites. Unicage advises Users to visit the privacy policy of such pages, as well as their terms and conditions.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">13. CHANGES TO THE PRIVACY POLICY</h2>
          <p>To ensure the adequacy of the document, Unicage reserves the right to review this Policy at any time it deems appropriate, so it is recommended that Users check this privacy policy regularly and/or each time they access the Website.</p>
        </section>

      </div>
